cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper analyzes the coexistence performance of Wi-Fi and cellular networks in the unlicensed spectrum, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a model to find the optimal contention window size of cellular SCBSs, which involves information theory concepts such as throughput and traffic densities. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the total throughput of both networks, which can be related to multimedia applications that require high bandwidth. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may touch upon security concerns related to the coexistence of Wi-Fi and cellular networks in the unlicensed spectrum. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a model that combines the time-domain behavior of a cellular SCBS and a Wi-Fi access point, which can be related to systems and control.
